5937 /******************************************************************************/
5938 /* For a painless codes migration between the STM32F0xx device product */
5939 /* lines, the aliases defined below are put in place to overcome the */
5940 /* differences in the interrupt handlers and IRQn definitions. */
5941 /* No need to update developed interrupt code when moving across */
5942 /* product lines within the same STM32F0 Family */
5943 /******************************************************************************/
5944 
5945 /* Aliases for __IRQn */
5946 #define ADC1_IRQn ADC1_COMP_IRQn
5947 #define DMA1_Ch1_IRQn DMA1_Channel1_IRQn
5948 #define DMA1_Ch2_3_DMA2_Ch1_2_IRQn DMA1_Channel2_3_IRQn
5949 #define DMA1_Ch4_7_DMA2_Ch3_5_IRQn DMA1_Channel4_5_6_7_IRQn
5950 #define DMA1_Channel4_5_IRQn DMA1_Channel4_5_6_7_IRQn
5951 #define PVD_IRQn PVD_VDDIO2_IRQn
5952 #define VDDIO2_IRQn PVD_VDDIO2_IRQn
5953 #define RCC_IRQn RCC_CRS_IRQn
5954 #define TIM6_IRQn TIM6_DAC_IRQn
5955 #define USART3_6_IRQn USART3_4_IRQn
5956 #define USART3_8_IRQn USART3_4_IRQn
5957 
5958 
5959 /* Aliases for __IRQHandler */
5960 #define ADC1_IRQHandler ADC1_COMP_IRQHandler
5961 #define DMA1_Ch1_IRQHandler DMA1_Channel1_IRQHandler
5962 #define DMA1_Ch2_3_DMA2_Ch1_2_IRQHandler DMA1_Channel2_3_IRQHandler
5963 #define DMA1_Ch4_7_DMA2_Ch3_5_IRQHandler DMA1_Channel4_5_6_7_IRQHandler
5964 #define DMA1_Channel4_5_IRQHandler DMA1_Channel4_5_6_7_IRQHandler
5965 #define PVD_IRQHandler PVD_VDDIO2_IRQHandler
5966 #define VDDIO2_IRQHandler PVD_VDDIO2_IRQHandler
5967 #define RCC_IRQHandler RCC_CRS_IRQHandler
5968 #define TIM6_IRQHandler TIM6_DAC_IRQHandler
5969 #define USART3_6_IRQHandler USART3_4_IRQHandler
5970 #define USART3_8_IRQHandler USART3_4_IRQHandler
5971 
5972 
5973 #ifdef __cplusplus
5974 }
5975 #endif /* __cplusplus */
5976 
5977 #endif /* STM32F072xB_H */
